      p There are no striking differences between the United States and New Zealand in ordinary social life, and you should find it easy to get along. The New Zealand accent may seem strange to you so don&rsquo;t be surprised if they also smile at your accent and language. They will probably call you Yanks or Yankees, whether you come from the North or from the South, and will say you have a Yankee accent even if you speak with a South Carolina drawl. Women will be pleased, but will think it a little strange, when you say &ldquo;yes ma&rsquo;am&rdquo; to them, though men will not think it strange to hear &ldquo;yes sir.&rdquo;
      p Speaking of women, it is taken for granted that you will be discreet in your dealings with New Zealand girls.
