      p.noindent Many of them are engaged or married to men who are fighting overseas. Do not take advantage of their loneliness. Remember that New Zealand is a small country with a small population. Any sort of scandal travels very quickly. Regard yourself not only as an ambassador for Uncle Sam, but as a soldier and a gentleman.
      p Your recently increased pay will go a long way in New Zealand where prices are comparatively low and where the rate of exchange is in your favor. So you may find yourself with more spending money than most New Zealand men, whether soldiers or civilians. Don&rsquo;t toss it around. It won&rsquo;t make you popular and can very easily make for hard feelings.
