      p.heading <span>The Maoris.</span> The New Zealand natives are called the Maoris, pronounced &ldquo;mow&rdquo; to rhyme with &ldquo;cow&rdquo; and &ldquo;rie.&rdquo; The correct plural is Maori but you will find most people putting an <em>s</em> on the end. These New Zealand natives are first cousins of the Hawaiians and are a proud, tough, fighting race who have won a status of complete equality with the white people in New Zealand, so never think of them or refer to them as natives or regard them as having any inferior status.
